For an example of the functionality, see this StackExchange link: http://blog.stackoverflow.com/2010/08/tag-folksonomy-and-tag-synonyms/

As a tag library grows, it becomes more and more unwieldy with near-duplicate terms (js vs. javascript) and no mechanism to determine which tags should rightly be applied to an issue.  Building on the strength of JIRA and Confluence, you could provide the features described above to allow tags to have descriptions added to them which show when adding a tag to provide additional information when deciding which tags to assign.  You could also provide tag redirection so that similar tags can be redirected to one tag (in searching, etc) rather than being separated and distinct.

