JIRA needs some way to prohibit changing the reporter in projects with restricted access. We want reporter always to mean "original reporter." If an issue is being moved and this cannot be retained, we want to stop the move. There doesn't seem to be a way to do this. Even if no users have "Modify Reporter" permission, reporters can still be modified. In fact, if I take away "Modify Reporter" permission in our secure (restricted-access) projects, the reporter is *always* changed, even if the original reporter is a member of the target project. At least this is the behavior I see when I move a single issue (outside the bulk updater).

If moving a single issue, JIRA spells out exactly what will happen to the reporter before an action is taken. The user performing the explicitly confirms the change in this case. But this still leaves open the possibility of mistakes.

For bulk moves, the matter is obscured and more dangerous. See https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-14385. The user can say to retain the reporter, but this will only be done if it is possible. Otherwise the default reporter (which *must* be specified for the bulk move) will be used.

